@startuml fig-udp-vs-tcp-loss-topo
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam roundcorner 12

title Mininet Topology — UDP vs TCP Under Packet Loss

rectangle "**h1**\n10.0.0.1/24\n(sender)" as h1 #FFE0B2

rectangle "**s1**\nOVS Switch" as s1 #90CAF9

rectangle "**h2**\n10.0.0.2/24\n(receiver)" as h2 #C8E6C9

h1 -right--> s1 : <color:#E53935>loss = 20%</color>\nTCLink
s1 -right--> h2 : <color:#E53935>loss = 20%</color>\nTCLink

note bottom of h1 #FFF9C4
  udp_sender.py → port 9091
  tcp_sender.py → port 9092
  Sends 200 messages
end note

note bottom of h2 #FFF9C4
  udp_receiver.py ← port 9091
  tcp_receiver.py ← port 9092
  Counts received messages
end note

note top of s1 #FFEBEE
  Artificial loss configured
  via TCLink (configurable %)
end note

legend bottom
  The scenario demonstrates that UDP loses
  messages under packet loss whilst TCP
  delivers the full stream transparently.
  Loss percentage is configurable in topo.py.
  Run with: sudo ./run.sh [loss%]
endlegend
@enduml
